params.data: Packed structure with pool, user, cdp, weth collateral to move, and maximum Dai price to pay for fyDai.
params.fyDaiAmount: fyDai debt to move from Yield to MakerDAO.

exportCdpPosition(address,uint256,uint25.details: Transfer debt and collateral from Yield to MakerDAO Needs vat.hope(splitter.address, { from: user }); Needs controller.addDelegate(splitter.address, { from: user });

params.fyDaiAmount: fyDai debt to move from Yield to MakerDAO.
params.maxFYDaiPrice: Maximum Dai price to pay for fyDai.
params.pool: The pool to trade in (and therefore fyDai series to migrate)
params.wethAmount: weth to move from Yield to MakerDAO. Needs to be high enough to collateralize the dai debt in MakerDAO, and low enough to make sure that debt left in Yield is also collateralized.

exportCdpPositionCheck(uint256).details: Determine whether all approvals and signatures are in place for `exportCdpPosition`.

params.cdp: CDP Vault to export to. If `return[0]` is `false`, calling `cdpMgr.cdpAllow(cdp, exportCdpProxy.address, 1)` will set the MakerDAO approval. If `return[1]` is `false`, `exportCdpPositionWithSignature` must be called with a controller signature. If `return` is `(true, true)`, `exportCdpPosition` won't fail because of missing approvals or signatures.

exportCdpPositionWithSignature(address,u.details: Transfer debt and collateral from Yield to MakerDAO Needs vat.hope(exportCdpProxy.address, { from: user });
